    public class FlickrImageDataset<IMAGE extends Image<?,IMAGE>>
extends ReadableListDataset<IMAGE,InputStream>
    Class to dynamically create image datasets from flickr through various api calls.

    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

                                                                              FlickrAPIToken token,
                                                                              String searchTerms)
                                                                       throws Exception
        Create an image dataset by searching flickr with the given search terms.
        Parameters:
        reader - the reader with which to load the images
        token - the flickr api authentication token
        searchTerms - the search terms; space separated. Prepending a term with a "-" means that the term should not appear.

      • create

        public static <IMAGE extends Image<?,IMAGE>> FlickrImageDataset<IMAGE> create(InputStreamObjectReader<IMAGE> reader,
                                                                              FlickrAPIToken token,
                                                                              String searchTerms,
                                                                              int number)
                                                                       throws Exception
        Create an image dataset by searching flickr with the given search terms. The number of images can be limited to a subset.
        Parameters:
        reader - the reader with which to load the images
        token - the flickr api authentication token
        searchTerms - the search terms; space separated. Prepending a term with a "-" means that the term should not appear.
        number - the maximum number of images to add to the dataset. Setting to 0 or less will attempt to use all the images.
        Returns:
        a FlickrImageDataset created from the given url
        Throws:
        Exception - if an error occurs
